<DocsLayout title="Integrations" section="Company Setup">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Field Promax integrates with several third-party services to automate workflows, sync data,
    and reduce manual tasks. Supported integrations include QuickBooks Online, QuickBooks Desktop,
    Google Calendar, Stripe, Xero, and Mailparser.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>QuickBooks Online:</strong> Click <strong>Sync with QuickBooks</strong> in the top right</li>
    <li><strong>Google Calendar / Stripe:</strong> Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Integrations</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Xero:</strong> Click <strong>Sync with Xero</strong> in the top right</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>QuickBooks Online</h2>
  <img src="/images/company-setup/integrations_01.png" alt="QuickBooks Integration" />
  <ul>
    <li>Click <strong>Sync with QuickBooks</strong> to connect your account</li>
    <li>Field Promax syncs Customers, Sub-Customers, Products, Projects, Class, and Estimates</li>
    <li>Convert work orders in Field Promax to Invoices in QuickBooks</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>QuickBooks Desktop</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Syncs via the <strong>Web Connector</strong> program included with QuickBooks Desktop</li>
    <li>Set up automatic sync at preset intervals</li>
    <li>Syncs Customers, Sub-Customers, Products, and Class</li>
    <li>Convert work orders to Invoices in QuickBooks</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Google Calendar</h2>
  <img src="/images/company-setup/googlecalendar_05.webp" alt="Google Calendar Integration" />
  <p>Integrate with Google Calendar to keep schedules synchronized:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Integrations</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>Sign in with Google</strong></li>
    <li>Enter your Google account credentials</li>
    <li>Allow Field Promax to sync with your calendar</li>
    <li>Your Google account appears in <strong>Connected Calendars</strong></li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    New and modified work orders automatically appear in your Google Calendar with a summarized view of all schedules.
  </p>

  <h2>Stripe</h2>
  <img src="/images/company-setup/integrations_02.webp" alt="Stripe Integration" />
  <ul>
    <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Integrations</strong></li>
    <li>Follow the steps to connect your Stripe account</li>
    <li>Once connected, collect and record payments directly from web or mobile app</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Xero</h2>
  <img src="/images/company-setup/integrations_02.png" alt="Xero Integration" />
  <ul>
    <li>Click <strong>Sync with Xero</strong> to connect</li>
    <li>Field Promax syncs Customers and Products with Xero</li>
    <li>Convert work orders to Invoices in Xero</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Mailparser</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Convert standardized emails into work orders automatically</li>
    <li>Contact Field Promax support for setup assistance</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>User Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Only <strong>Administrators</strong> can sync with QuickBooks or Xero</li>
    <li>Google Calendar updates in real-time with new work orders</li>
    <li>Stripe payments are recorded automatically when processed</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Sync regularly</strong> with QuickBooks or Xero to keep financial data accurate.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Set up automatic sync</strong> in QuickBooks Desktop to keep data current.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Monitor your Stripe integration</strong> to ensure successful payment transactions.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
